TITLE: Multipart Upload for Large Files in Vercel Blob (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the new multipart option for reliable uploads of medium and large files in Vercel Blob, including examples with Node.js streams and ReadableStreams.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/storage/blob/main/test/next/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-08_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const blob = await put('file.png', file, {
  access: 'public',
  multipart: true, // `false` by default
});

// and:
const blob = await upload('file.png', file, {
  access: 'public',
  handleUploadUrl: '/api/upload',
  multipart: true,
});

// Using Node.js stream
import { createReadStream } from 'node:fs';

const blob = await vercelBlob.put(
  'elon.mp4',
  // this works ðŸ‘, it will gradually read the file from the system and upload it
  createReadStream('/users/Elon/me.mp4'),
  { access: 'public', multipart: true },
);

// Using ReadableStream
const response = await fetch(
  'https://example-files.online-convert.com/video/mp4/example_big.mp4',
);

const blob = await vercelBlob.put(
  'example_big.mp4',
  // this works too ðŸ‘, it will gradually read the file from internet and upload it
  response.body,
  { access: 'public', multipart: true },
);
```

