TITLE: Manual Multipart Upload with Vercel Blob (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the new advanced multipart upload methods in Vercel Blob to manually control the upload process in multiple steps.
SOURCE: https://github.com/vercel/storage/blob/main/test/next/CHANGELOG.md#2025-04-08_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const { key, uploadId } = await vercelBlob.createMultipartUpload(
  'big-file.txt',
  { access: 'public' },
);

const part1 = await vercelBlob.uploadPart(fullPath, 'first part', {
  access: 'public',
  key,
  uploadId,
  partNumber: 1,
});

const part2 = await vercelBlob.uploadPart(fullPath, 'second part', {
  access: 'public',
  key,
  uploadId,
  partNumber: 2,
});

const blob = await vercelBlob.completeMultipartUpload(
  fullPath,
  [part1, part2],
  {
    access: 'public',
    key,
    uploadId,
  }
);
```

